# iOS DevOps playbook (agent order)

When the user asks to set up **Git**, **CI/CD**, **GitHub Actions**, or **pipeline** for an **Xcode iOS** app (new or existing), run this sequence without skipping validation steps.

## 0. Reuse across repos (humans + Cursor)

- **Canonical template:** **Pipeline-Generic** (this repo or a fork). Copy **infrastructure only** from a local clone‚Äîsee **`SETUP_IOS_DEVOPS_KIT.md`** for `rsync` paths. **Do not** copy the template sample app folder **`PipelineGeneric/`** into another product unless replacing that product‚Äôs sources.
- **Single Agent message (copy + wire + optional push):** developer pastes **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_APPLY_TEMPLATE_PROMPT.txt`** with **TEMPLATE_ROOT** = absolute path to Pipeline-Generic and **TARGET_REMOTE_URL** = empty app remote (HTTPS/SSH) or skip. If they only give the **app‚Äôs clone URL**, clone/open that repo first, then apply template from **TEMPLATE_ROOT**.
- **Files already in the app repo:** developer pastes **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_BOOTSTRAP_PROMPT.txt`** (through **`END BOOTSTRAP`**) so you substitute **PipelineGeneric** / paths / bundle id across workflows, **`fastlane/Fastfile`**, CodeQL, code health, **`.swiftlint.yml`**, **`.swiftformat`**.
- **Flat manifest + ‚ÄúI only have a URL‚Äù routing:** **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_REUSE.md`**.
- **Legacy zip folder:** If teams still use **`ios-devops-cursor-kit/`**, merge **contents** into the app root (`rsync -a kit/ ./`), append **`GITIGNORE_APPEND.txt`**, copy root prompt/setup docs, then **delete** the nested **`ios-devops-cursor-kit/`**‚Äî**GitHub Actions only uses `.github/` at the repository root.**
- **During bootstrap:** if both **`ios-devops-cursor-kit/.github/`** and **root `.github/`** exist, **remove** `ios-devops-cursor-kit/` (after confirming root files are complete)‚Äîdo **not** recreate root files from the nested folder again.
- **This reference repo (Pipeline-Generic):** canonical entry workflows are **`ios.yml`** (orchestrator) and reusable **`ios-job-*.yml`** + **`ios-release.yml`** ‚Äî see **`github-actions-ios-ci.mdc`** for the exact DAG.

## 1. Discover

- Locate `*.xcodeproj` and a **shared** scheme under **`*.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/`** (committed ‚Äî **not** only under gitignored `xcuserdata/`; CI‚Äôs `xcodebuild` will not see user-only schemes).
- From `project.pbxproj`: `PRODUCT_NAME` / app name, `PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER`, `IPHONEOS_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET`.

## 2. Remote repository ‚Äî automate (developer only supplies the URL)

**Goal:** Minimize manual Git for the developer. They should **not** have to run `git remote add` and `git push` themselves unless authentication blocks the agent.

**Early** (when starting Git/DevOps, or right before you finish local Git in ¬ß3), **ask once**:

- Paste the **clone URL** for an **empty** remote repo (HTTPS or SSH), **or**
- Say **skip / no remote yet** ‚Äî then tell them: create an empty repo on GitHub, GitLab, Azure DevOps, etc. (avoid adding a README on the host if they want zero merge friction), then **paste the URL in chat**; you will run the Git commands on the next message.

**When a URL is provided** and `main` (or the repo‚Äôs current default branch) has at least one commit:

1. Resolve remote name: default **`origin`** unless they specify another.
2. If that remote is missing: `git remote add <name> <url>`.
3. If it exists but the URL differs: `git remote set-url <name> <url>`.
4. Push: `git push -u <name> <branch>` where `<branch>` is `git branch --show-current` (expect `main`).

**When the clone URL appears anywhere in the conversation**, run the git commands in the repo‚Äôs terminal **in this session** before you call the bootstrap ‚Äúdone.‚Äù **Do not** end with a checklist that tells the developer to run `git remote add` / `git push` themselves if you have shell access and they gave a URL‚Äî**you** run those commands first.

If they **have not** pasted a URL yet, **do not** write ‚Äúnot done by the agent‚Äù / ‚Äúyou still must add remote‚Äù as a permanent handoff. Instead **ask once** for the empty repo‚Äôs HTTPS or SSH URL and say you will run add + push as soon as they paste it (or they may say **skip remote**).

If **push fails** (auth, etc.), then explain the fix and offer to **retry** after they authenticate‚Äîonly then is manual intervention expected.

If **push succeeds**, confirm briefly. **Never** imply the project is on the host until push has succeeded.

If **push fails** (auth, permissions, non‚Äìfast-forward): report the error, give **targeted** fixes (e.g. `gh auth login`, HTTPS PAT / credential helper, SSH agent and `ssh -T git@github.com`), and **retry** after they fix auth if they ask. Do not default to `--force` or `--force-with-lease` unless they **explicitly** want to overwrite the remote history.

**Reminder:** **local Git ‚âÝ hosted remote** until `remote` is set **and** `push` succeeds.

## 3. Git (local)

- If no `.git`: init on repo root, `git branch -M main`, add Xcode `.gitignore` (see `git-xcode-bootstrap.mdc`), initial commit.
- Immediately after the first commit (or if commits already exist), **perform ¬ß2 remote steps** when the developer has pasted a URL in this session; if they have not, **ask for the URL** (or confirm skip) before closing the handoff.

## 4. CI workflow

**This repository (Pipeline-Generic) ‚Äî use as the live pattern:**

- **`.github/workflows/ios.yml`** ‚Äî orchestrator (`workflow_dispatch` optional TestFlight checkbox, push/PR to `main` and `master`).
- Reusable callees: **`ios-job-lint.yml`**, **`ios-job-security.yml`**, **`ios-job-simulator-artifact.yml`**, **`ios-job-test.yml`**, **`ios-release.yml`** (Match + `gym`, optional upload step).
- Standalone: **`ios-code-health.yml`**, **`codeql-swift.yml`**, **`.github/dependabot.yml`**.
- Details and paths: **`github-actions-ios-ci.mdc`**.

**Starting a different app (greenfield or kit merge):**

- Substitute **`.xcodeproj` path**, **scheme**, **bundle id**, artifact names, and **`hashFiles(...)`** paths from `project.pbxproj` / folder layout.
- Align **`.swiftlint.yml` `included:`** with real source directories.
- Ensure **`DerivedDataCI/`**, **`fastlane/keys/`**, **`vendor/bundle/`** are gitignored when CI uses them (see repo `.gitignore`).

## 4b. Release / TestFlight

**This repository:**

- **`ios-release.yml`** is **`workflow_call` only** ‚Äî invoked by **`ios.yml`** on **`main`/`master` push** or **`workflow_dispatch`**.
- Signing: **Fastlane Match** + **`bundle exec fastlane staging_build`**; optional **`upload_testflight_ipa`** when the orchestrator passes **`upload_to_testflight: true`** (manual run with checkbox).
- Required secrets are documented in **`README.md`** (not P12/profile-in-YAML).

**Other templates (e.g. raw kit `ios-release.yml`):**

- May use **tag** triggers (`v*`), **base64 P12 + profile** in secrets, and **`xcodebuild` archive/export** in YAML. If you copy that variant into another repo, follow **that** file‚Äôs comments for secrets‚Äîdo not assume it matches this repo‚Äôs Match-based **`ios-release.yml`**.

## 5. After green CI

- Explain artifact download ‚Üí **rename unzipped folder to `App.app`** ‚Üí `simctl install` / `launch` (see `ios-ci-artifact-simulator.mdc`).

## 5b. Handoff wording ‚Äî Git remote vs release

- **Git remote + push** are **your** job when a URL is supplied (¬ß2‚Äì¬ß3). **Do not** lump them into ‚Äúnot done by the agent‚Äù or ‚Äúyou still do this‚Äù alongside Apple signing.
- **Release / TestFlight** require **repository secrets** the agent cannot set‚Äî**those** may be described as still on the developer (see **`README.md`** and workflow YAML). Keep the two topics **separate** so users are not told they must manually push when you should push for them.

## Out of scope unless requested

- Do not run or ‚Äúfix‚Äù **release** on behalf of the user without the signing material their workflow expects (e.g. Match repo + password + ASC API key **for this repo**; or Distribution cert + App Store profile + team ID **for P12-style workflows**).

## Reuse on another project

- **Preferred:** Clone **Pipeline-Generic**, then from the **target app** root follow **`SETUP_IOS_DEVOPS_KIT.md`** (rsync `.cursor/`, `.github/`, `.semgrep/`, `fastlane/`, `Gemfile*`, lint configs, root `CURSOR_*` / `SETUP_*` / `GITIGNORE_APPEND.txt`). Paste **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_APPLY_TEMPLATE_PROMPT.txt`** or **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_BOOTSTRAP_PROMPT.txt`** per **`ios-devops-reuse-prompts.mdc`**.
- **Legacy:** **`ios-devops-cursor-kit`** zip/folder ‚Äî **`rsync -a kit/ ./`**, then **remove** nested **`ios-devops-cursor-kit/`** (see **`SETUP_IOS_DEVOPS_KIT.md`**). **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_REUSE.md`** lists the flat file manifest.
- If nothing was copied yet, copy `.cursor/rules`, `.github/` (workflows + scripts + dependabot), `.semgrep/`, `Gemfile`, `Gemfile.lock`, `fastlane`, `.swiftlint.yml`, `.swiftformat`, then run this playbook with names from **`project.pbxproj`** and shared schemes.
